<body ><div id="Section 1" class="mktEditable" ><p><strong><span style="font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">Please <u>discard</u> if you have existing repair and overhaul (R&amp;O) contracts with agreed to pricing.</span></strong></p>
<p><img src="https://pages3.honeywell.com/rs/641-QIX-912/images/honeywell_emailheader_logo.png" alt="" width="140" height="50" /></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;"><br /></span></strong></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Dear Honeywell R&amp;O Customer, </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">At Honeywell, we are constantly looking for ways to simplify and improve the repair and overhaul experience for you &ndash; our customer. With that in mind we are changing the way we communicate unfunded R&amp;O purchase orders received that are subject to universal flat rates* (UFR) or Time &amp; Material (T&amp;M) pricing. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Here are the steps to take prior to shipping your repair unit to Honeywell:</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Log into the customer portal at <a href="http://www.myaerospace.com">www.myaerospace.com</a><br /> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Select the &ldquo;Online Ordering&rdquo; application <br /> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Select your account from the dropdown menu, click on repair part type, and enter or search for the part number<br /> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enter the UFR pricing amount on your purchase order and include with your repair unit or email to <a href="mailto:aerorepairs@Honeywell.com">aerorepairs@Honeywell.com</a>. That&rsquo;s it!<br /> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If pricing is not available, enter an unfunded (zero dollar) amount on your purchase order and include with your repair unit or email to <a href="mailto:aerorepairs@Honeywell.com">aerorepairs@Honeywell.com</a>. <br /> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">6)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Once the unfunded purchase order is received, T&amp;M pricing is applied. You will receive an auto-generated email requesting you to amend your purchase order so we may induct the unit. <br /> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">7)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Once Honeywell receives your funded PO, we will begin processing your repair unit immediately. <strong>No further action is needed from you.<br /> </strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">8)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When your repair is completed, we will include a copy of the Caf&eacute;/Service report in the shipment. This report is also provided to units returned as &ldquo;No Fault Found&rdquo;, along with a &ldquo;Test Teardown &amp; Evaluation&rdquo; fee.<br /> <br /> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Here&rsquo;s a sample of the email message. <br /></span></p>
<p align="center"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong><em>In order to induct</em></strong><strong><em> and process your unit,</em></strong><strong><em> please<br />amend your PO with the T&amp;M pricing.</em></strong><strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong> <br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">When you reply to these email messages, please use the &ldquo;reply all&rdquo; email function so we may continue to capture your Reference Case Number listed in the subject line. The reference case number helps maintain a record of all customer and repair communications associated with the unit. <br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">If we don&rsquo;t hear back from you, we&rsquo;ll send you a <u>reminder after 5 calendar days</u>. If we failure to receive any response from you <u>after 10 calendar days</u>, the repair unit will be returned to you in an &ldquo;As Is&rdquo; condition. <br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">If you have any questions, please contact your Honeywell Customer Business Manager. <br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Best regards,<br /><br />Honeywell Aerospace <br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12px;"><em>* Universal flat rates include all minor modifications, overhaul rework instructions, and service bulletins that do not require a change of material number -- <strong>at no extra cost to you</strong>. </em><em>Honeywell does reserve the right to reject repair materials under the flat rate program if deemed to have &lsquo;excessive&rsquo; repair requirements and/or are beyond economical repair.</em></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span></p></div>
